%h2 Buttons

%p The following buttons, and corresponding classes, should work on any element. Style variants include large and small buttons, on top of the default size, as well as disabled styles, by way of a class or <code>disabled</code> attribute.

%ul.sg-value-list
  %li
    Large Button
    %code.sg-value-offset .btn-large
  %li
    Small Button
    %code.sg-value-offset .btn-small
  %li
    Active Button
    %code.sg-value-offset .btn-active
  %li
    Disabled Button Attribute
    %code.sg-value-offset [disabled]
  %li
    Disabled Button Class
    %code.sg-value-offset .btn-disabled


-# ========================================
-# Default buttons

%section.pad-bottom

  %h4 Default Buttons
  %p Default buttons are identified with the <code>.btn-default</code> class.

  %a.btn-default.btn-large(href="#") Default Button
  %a.btn-default.btn-large.btn-disabled(href="#") Default Button

  %a.btn-default(href="#") Default Button
  %a.btn-default.btn-disabled(href="#") Default Button

  %a.btn-default.btn-small(href="#") Default Button
  %a.btn-default.btn-small.btn-disabled(href="#") Default Button

